quran[18]{c,v,t,f}:
  37,160,"Except the chosen servants of Allāh [who do not share in that sin]."
  37,161,"So indeed, you [disbelievers] and whatever you worship,"
  37,162,"You cannot tempt [anyone] away from Him"
  43,49,"And they said [to Moses], "
  43,50,"But when We removed from them the affliction, at once they broke their word."
  43,51,"And Pharaoh called out among his people; he said, "
  44,34,"Indeed, these [disbelievers] are saying,"
  44,35,""
  44,36,"Then bring [back] our forefathers, if you should be truthful."
  45,25,"And when Our verses are recited to them as clear evidences, their argument is only that they say, "
  45,26,"Say, "
  45,27,"And to Allāh belongs the dominion of the heavens and the earth. And the Day the Hour appears - that Day the falsifiers will lose."
  46,13,"Indeed, those who have said, "
  46,14,"Those are the companions of Paradise, abiding eternally therein as reward for what they used to do."
  46,15,"And We have enjoined upon man, to his parents, good treatment. His mother carried him with hardship and gave birth to him with hardship, and his gestation and weaning [period] is thirty months. [He grows] until, when he reaches maturity and reaches [the age of] forty years, he says, ",footnotes:1:Literally, "gather within me the utmost strength and ability."
  47,4,"So when you meet those who disbelieve [in battle], strike [their] necks until, when you have inflicted slaughter upon them, then secure [their] bonds,{1} and either [confer] favor{2} afterwards or ransom [them] until the war lays down its burdens.{3} That [is the command]. And if Allāh had willed, He could have taken vengeance upon them [Himself], but [He ordered armed struggle] to test some of you by means of others. And those who are killed in the cause of Allāh - never will He waste their deeds.",footnotes:1:[i.e., take those remaining as captives.],footnotes:2:[i.e., release them without ransom.],footnotes:3:[i.e., its armor, machinery, etc., meaning \"until the war is over.\"]
  47,5,"He will guide them and amend their condition"
  47,6,"And admit them to Paradise, which He has made known to them."
